From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 10:30:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: rockchip: align Rock Pi 4 PCIe with working
 Armbian

A Rock Pi 4A booted with Armbian 23.11.1 / Linux 6.1.63 detects the
JMicron JMB58x AHCI controller on the RK3399 PCIe root port.  Armbian's
exact Rock Pi 4 PCIe DTS patch for that image adds four properties that
are absent from the mainline Rock Pi 4 DTS used by the Talos RockPi build:

  - regulator-min-microvolt = <3300000> on vcc3v3_pcie;
  - regulator-max-microvolt = <3300000> on vcc3v3_pcie;
  - vpcie12v-supply = <&vcc12v_dcin>;
  - bus-scan-delay-ms = <1500>;

Mirror those properties to align with the known-good Armbian
image.  The 12 V supply is the board input rail and is always on, but
wiring it into the PCIe node matches the working DT and removes the
"no vpcie12v regulator found" path.  The scan delay is consumed by
Armbian's Rockchip PCIe host patch and matches the successful boot log:

  rockchip-pcie f8000000.pcie: wait 1500 ms (from device tree) before bus scan

This is a local Rock Pi 4 PCIe compatibility patch for the Talos
RockPi build.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4.dtsi | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4.dtsi
@@ -110,7 +110,9 @@
 		pinctrl-0 = <&pcie_pwr_en>;
 		regulator-name = "vcc3v3_pcie";
 		regulator-always-on;
 		regulator-boot-on;
+		regulator-min-microvolt = <3300000>;
+		regulator-max-microvolt = <3300000>;
 		vin-supply = <&vcc5v0_sys>;
 	};
 
@@ -532,10 +534,12 @@
 };
 
 &pcie0 {
+	bus-scan-delay-ms = <1500>;
 	ep-gpios = <&gpio4 RK_PD3 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
 	num-lanes = <4>;
 	pinctrl-0 = <&pcie_clkreqnb_cpm>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
+	vpcie12v-supply = <&vcc12v_dcin>;
 	vpcie0v9-supply = <&vcc_0v9>;
 	vpcie1v8-supply = <&vcc_1v8>;
 	vpcie3v3-supply = <&vcc3v3_pcie>;
